messages.content: hi there , i am trying to create a menu and i cannot find any of my existing recipes in the choose a recipe tab

Hi. To create an a la carte menu, your recipe creations must me costed and priced. Otherwise they will not appear in the drop down. Uncosted and unpriced recipes will however appear when you create a set menu (for an event etc)
ok, thank you very much
Hey , is there a way to add new items in the inventory after the first stocktaking to increase their value ? ex: i have 2kg of strawberries and i buy 2kg more
You add invoices
So at tbe end you have opening stock + invoices - closing stock
oh i see, so when i add a new invoice , will be able to add new materials ?
To add new materials you can do so in the ingredients tab or in your recipes directly.
If you like to contact us through whatsup or viber we can discuss exactly
ok great, i am going to text you again when i am about to start the inventory so you can help me a bit
Word of advice. As a step one you should start directly with recipe creation. All the ingredients you add in a recipe will be added automatically to you stock
So less work
Oh

Sub recipes become ingredients. So starting with subrecipes will give you ingregients to use in your recipes

Greece at the moment
Ok

is there a way i can gather all the ingredients that have no price yet in a single list?
Home page under the main ingredients button you will find a list of all the uncosted ingredients
is there a way i cant print that ?
No
ok , thanks a lot
have a nice day
